Package org.neo4j.csv.reader

Interface Extractor<T>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Cloneable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Extractors.AbstractExtractor, Extractors.AbstractSingleAnyValueExtractor, Extractors.AbstractSingleValueExtractor, Extractors.ArrayExtractor, Extractors.BooleanArrayExtractor, Extractors.BooleanExtractor, Extractors.ByteArrayExtractor, Extractors.ByteExtractor, Extractors.CharExtractor, Extractors.DateExtractor, Extractors.DateTimeExtractor, Extractors.DoubleArrayExtractor, Extractors.DoubleExtractor, Extractors.DurationExtractor, Extractors.FloatArrayExtractor, Extractors.FloatExtractor, Extractors.IntArrayExtractor, Extractors.IntExtractor, Extractors.LocalDateTimeExtractor, Extractors.LocalTimeExtractor, Extractors.LongArrayExtractor, Extractors.LongExtractor, Extractors.PointExtractor, Extractors.ShortArrayExtractor, Extractors.ShortExtractor, Extractors.StringArrayExtractor, Extractors.StringExtractor, Extractors.TimeExtractor
    public interface Extractor<T>
extends Cloneable
    Extracts a value from a part of a char[] into any type of value, f.ex. a Extractors.string(), long or Extractors.intArray(). An Extractor is mutable for the single purpose of ability to reuse its value instance. Consider extracting a primitive int - Sub-interfaces and implementations can and should specify specific accessors for the purpose of performance and less garbage, f.ex. where an IntExtractor could have an accessor method for getting the extracted value as primitive int, to avoid auto-boxing which would arise from calling value().
    See Also:
    for a collection of very common extractors.

      • extract

        boolean extract​(char[] data,
                int offset,
                int length,
                boolean hadQuotes,
                CSVHeaderInformation optionalData)
        Extracts value of type T from the given character data.
        Parameters:
        data - characters in a buffer.
        offset - offset into the buffer where the value starts.
        length - number of characters from the offset to extract.
        hadQuotes - whether or not there were skipped characters, f.ex. quotation.
        optionalData - optional data to be used for spatial or temporal values or null if csv header did not use it
        Returns:
        true if a value was extracted, otherwise false.

      • normalize

        Extractor<?> normalize()
        Normalizes this extractor to that of a broader type, if possible. E.g. an extractor for int becomes long. This normalization should match higher levels of type systems, like Cypher.
        Returns:
        an extractor which potentially is of a broader type than this extractor.
